     <img src="/images/main/about.jpg"/>
     <h3>
      Spreading the Word
     </h3>
     <p>
      University Communications is a team of professionals responsible for creating and managing the marketing and messaging of the University of California, Riverside.
     </p>
     <p>
      University Communications consists of five separate departments:
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       <h4>
        <a href="http://marketing.ucr.edu" style="color: #2668b2;">
         Marketing
        </a>
       </h4>
       <p>
        UCR Marketing is responsible for managing the university’s brand and visual identity. Our team of professionals plays a key coordinating role among all who communicate the university’s message and identity.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h4>
        <a href="http://mediarelations.ucr.edu/" style="color: #2668b2;">
         News and Information
        </a>
       </h4>
       <p>
        UCR News and Information is responsible for interactions between the university and the media. In addition to writing and pitching press releases to media, the department produces the quarterly UCR Magazine and bi-monthly Inside UCR faculty and staff newspaper.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h4>
        <a href="http://videoproduction.ucr.edu/" style="color: #2668b2;">
         Video Production
        </a>
       </h4>
       <p>
        The video production unit creates professional videos to inspire pride, commitment, and investment in UC Riverside. We strive to capture the best of UCR and share it with the world via YouTube and other social platforms.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h4>
        <a href="http://creativedesign.ucr.edu/" style="color: #2668b2;">
         Creative Design Services
        </a>
       </h4>
       <p>
        Serving the campus’ graphic arts and design needs.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h4>
        Digital Content
       </h4>
       <p>
        The University Communications digital content team provides consultation services and training and offers best practices. The team is responsible for the words, design, and visual imagery of campus communications. The digital team also maintains the strategic direction and development of all university-wide social media accounts and provides consultation services and training and offers best practices.
       </p>
       <p style="color: #2668b2; font-weight: bold;">
        Social Media Tools
       </p>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="/downloads/SocialNetworkingPolicy.pdf">
          View the UCR Social Media Policy
         </a>
        </li>
        <li>
         <a href="/downloads/UCR%20Social%20Media%20Hashtag%20List.pdf">
          View the commonly used UCR Hashtags across campus
         </a>
        </li>
        <li>
         <a href="/downloads/Emergency%20Communications%20Social%20Policy.pdf">
          Download the UCR Social Media Emergency Communications Guidelines
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
       If you're thinking of starting a channel for your department, please review our Social Media Channel Checklist and contact Kelly McGrail -
       <a href="mailto:Kelly.mcgrail@ucr.edu">
        Kelly.mcgrail@ucr.edu
       </a>
       <p style="color: #2668b2; font-weight: bold;">
        Web content Tools
       </p>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="http://www.gorocketfuel.com/the-rocket-blog/5-best-practices-for-your-website-content-strategy/">
          5 Best Practices for Your Website Content Strategy, via RocketFuel
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="https://hingemarketing.com/blog/story/7-best-practices-for-website-copywriting">
          7 Best Practices for Website Copywriting, via Hinge Marketing
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="https://www.orbitmedia.com/blog/content-marketing-audit/">
          How to do a Content Marketing Audit in 8-Steps, via Orbit Media Solutions
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="http://contentmarketinginstitute.com/2014/01/online-content-best-practices-for-2014//">
          Best Practices for Online Content Success, via Content Marketing Institute
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
       <ul>
        <li>
         <a href="http://cms.ucr.edu/writing_web_content.html">
          View tips for writing for the web
         </a>
        </li>
       </ul>
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p style="color: #2668b2; font-weight: bold;">
      Responsive Web Content Strategy Training
     </p>
     <ul>
      <li>
       <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-UT0NAfS8Cw&amp;feature=youtu.be//">
        University Communications Training
       </a>
      </li>
     </ul>
     <br>
      <h3>
       Our Goals
      </h3>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <p>
         As a public institute, we strive to communicate fully with campus members and our partners.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <p>
         To create an environment that favors and supports the university.
        </p>
       </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>
       Our Objectives
      </h3>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <p>
         To maintain the higher standards of accuracy and professionalism in communication.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <p>
         To present a balanced and complete picture of UCR as a comprehensive research university.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <p>
         To raise awareness and understanding of the university's stature and the value of its activities.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <p>
         To use emerging and established media to communicate.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <p>
         To maintain a highly credible and responsive News and Information program.
        </p>
       </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>
       Our Publications and Programs
      </h3>
      <ul>
       <li>
        <h4>
         In the news
        </h4>
        <p>
         <a href="http://mediarelations.ucr.edu/inthenews.html">
          UCR in the News
         </a>
         , produced by University Communications, collects highlights of news coverage about UC Riverside and delivers it directly to your inbox. Subscribe by sending an email to
         <a href="mailto:news@ucr.edu?subject=Subscribe%20to%20In%20the%20News">
          news@ucr.edu
         </a>
         .
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         Events Calendar
        </h4>
        <p>
         A comprehensive list of the
         <a href="http://events.ucr.edu" target="_blank">
          happenings taking place at UC Riverside
         </a>
         .
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <a href="https://websites.ucr.edu/events-calendar">
         View the Events Calendar FAQs
        </a>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         Experts on demand
        </h4>
        <p>
         The university features dozens of
         <a href="http://www.ucr.edu/media/experts.html">
          faculty members who are experts in their fields
         </a>
         and who are happy to quickly respond to interview requests.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         UCR photo gallery
        </h4>
        <p>
         A collection of
         <a href="http://photos.ucr.edu/">
          photos of UCR people, places and things
         </a>
         for print and electronic publication.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         UCR magazine
        </h4>
        <p>
         <a href="http://ucrmagazine.ucr.edu/">
          UCR Magazine
         </a>
         is a quarterly campus magazine designed to keep readers engaged with UC Riverside.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         Inside UCR
        </h4>
        <p>
         <a href="http://ucrtoday.ucr.edu/inside-ucr">
          Inside UCR
         </a>
         is a weekly newspaper geared towards UCR's faculty and staff. It is published every Wednesday during the academic year.
        </p>
       </li>
       <li>
        <h4>
         Campus Map
        </h4>
        <p>
         The fully searchable online version of the
         <a href="http://campusmap.ucr.edu/">
          UCR Campus Map
         </a>
         is linked from every page within the UCR web site or directly from
         <a href="http://campusmap.ucr.edu/">
          campusmap.ucr.edu
         </a>
         . A
         <a href="http://campusmap.ucr.edu/map.pdf" title="PDF file: Campus Map">
          printable PDF
         </a>
         of the map is also available online. Paper copies of the map may be obtained upon entering campus from either of the parking kiosks.
        </p>
       </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="divided3">
